annotationA: Alanine--tRNA ligase, cytoplasmic; Catalyzes the attachment of alanine to tRNA(Ala) in a two-step reaction: alanine is first activated by ATP to form Ala- AMP and then transferred to the acceptor end of tRNA(Ala). Also edits incorrectly charged tRNA(Ala) via its editing domain; Belongs to the class-II aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase family
annotationB: Probable phenylalanine--tRNA ligase, mitochondrial; Is responsible for the charging of tRNA(Phe) with phenylalanine in mitochondrial translation
